{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_22fe2dc34d3c4399873a8ef9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Phase 5 Admin Wiring — Task Reference\n2\t\n3\t## Global Rules\n4\t- Working directory: `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment`\n5\t- These tasks depend on Phases 1-4 being complete\n6\t- Do NOT modify `app/utils/auth.ts`\n7\t- Do NOT remove `mock-data.ts` until ALL mock imports are eliminated\n8\t- Group 7 ordering (`5.1` → `5.2` → `5.3` and `5.5` after `5.1-5.4`) is binding for execution and should not be changed here.\n9\t\n10\t## Loop\n11\t- Implement: read this file, do Task N. Run `npx tsc --noEmit`. Commit.\n12\t- Review: read this file, check Task N. Fix or say \"all clean.\"\n13\t- Max 3 review rounds per task.\n14\t\n15\t---\n16\t\n17\t## Task 1: Wire Dynamic TTC List on Admin Pages\n18\t\n19\t- Slug: `ttc-list-wiring`\n20\t- Goal: Replace hardcoded TTC list placeholders with dynamic GCS-backed TTC list on all 3 admin pages.\n21\t\n22\t### Read These Files First\n23\t1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/route.ts` (full file) — has `DEFAULT_TTC_LIST_HTML` placeholder\n24\t2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_integrity/route.ts` (full file) — same pattern\n25\t3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_reports/route.ts` (full file) — same + `ttcCountryAndDates: '[]'`\n26\t4. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/admin.py` (lines 82-138) — `get_ttc_list_html()` to port\n27\t5. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts` — `readJson()`, `GCS_PATHS`\n28\t\n29\t### Changes Required\n30\t\n31\t**Create `app/utils/admin-helpers.ts`:**\n32\tPort `get_ttc_list_html()` from `admin.py:82-138`. Reads TTC list from GCS, generates `<option>` HTML. Also return raw JSON for `ttcCountryAndDates` parameter.\n33\t\n34\t```typescript\n35\timport { readJson, GCS_PATHS } from './gcs';\n36\t\n37\t/**\n38\t * Port of admin.py:82-138 get_ttc_list_html().\n39\t * @param userHomeCountry - ISO country code for filtering (optional). Legacy uses display_countries\n40\t *   field on each option to filter by user's home country (admin.py:102-105).\n41\t */\n42\texport async function getTtcListHtml(userHomeCountry?: string): Promise<{ html: string; json: string }> {\n43\t  const allOptions = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.TTC_COUNTRY_AND_DATES) as Array<Record<string, unknown>>;\n44\t\n45\t  // Filter options by display_countries (matching admin.py:102-105)\n46\t  const options = allOptions.filter(option => {\n47\t    if (userHomeCountry && Array.isArray(option.display_countries)) {\n48\t      return (option.display_countries as string[]).includes(userHomeCountry);\n49\t    }\n50\t    return true; // no filtering if no country or no display_countries field\n51\t  });\n52\t\n53\t  let optionsHtml = '';\n54\t  for (let i = 0; i < options.length; i++) {\n55\t    const option = options[i];\n56\t    const selected = i === options.length - 1 ? 'selected' : '';\n57\t    optionsHtml += `<option value=\"${option.value}\" ${selected}>${option.display}</option>`;\n58\t  }\n59\t  // Wrap in the same div structure as legacy admin.py:116-131\n60\t  const html = `<div class=\"mt-[15px] mb-[23px]\">\n61\t    <div class=\"tablebody\"><div name=\"ttc_list\" class=\"tablerow\">\n62\t      <div class=\"tablecell\"><label for=\"ttc_list\">TTC</label>\n63\t        <span class=\"smallertext\">Select the TTC from the dropdown</span></div>\n64\t      <div class=\"tablecell\">\n65\t        <select class=\"textbox\" id=\"ttc_list\" name=\"ttc_list\" onchange=\"load_table_data()\">\n66\t          ${optionsHtml}\n67\t        </select></div>\n68\t    </div></div></div>`;\n69\t  return { html, json: JSON.stringify(allOptions) }; // json uses ALL options (unfiltered, for client-side use)\n70\t}\n71\t```\n72\t\n73\t**Modify each of the 3 route files:** Replace hardcoded `DEFAULT_TTC_LIST_HTML` with `await getTtcListHtml()`.\n74\t\n75\tFor the reports page route (`ttc_applicants_reports/route.ts`), ALSO replace the hardcoded `ttcCountryAndDates: '[]'` with the `json` value returned from `getTtcListHtml()`:\n76\t```typescript\n77\tconst { html, json } = await getTtcListHtml();\n78\t// ... use html for DEFAULT_TTC_LIST_HTML replacement\n79\t// ... use json for ttcCountryAndDates: json\n80\t```\n81\t\n82\t### Verification\n83\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n84\t- Commit message: `feat: wire dynamic TTC list from GCS on admin pages`\n85\t\n86\t---\n87\t\n88\t## Task 2: Wire Last Updated Timestamps\n89\t\n90\t- Slug: `timestamps`\n91\t- Goal: Add real last-updated timestamps to admin pages (currently hardcoded or missing).\n92\t\n93\t### Read These Files First\n94\t1. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/admin.py` (lines 158-174) — `get_user_reporting_last_updated_datetime()` to port\n95\t2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts` — `getFileMetadata()` function\n96\t\n97\t### Changes Required\n98\t\n99\t**Step 1: Add helper to `app/utils/admin-helpers.ts`:**\n100\t```typescript\n101\texport async function getLastUpdatedTimestamps(): Promise<{\n102\t  user_summary_last_updated_datetime: string;\n103\t  user_integrity_last_updated_datetime: string;\n104\t}> {\n105\t  // Read file metadata for summary (by_form_type) and integrity (by_user) files\n106\t  // Use file.getMetadata() → top-level `updated` field\n107\t  // Format as 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS'\n108\t  // Handle file-not-found gracefully (return empty string)\n109\t}\n110\t```\n111\t\n112\t**Note:** Integrity reads from `_by_user` (not `_by_form_type`) — see plan for legacy inconsistency note.\n113\t\n114\t**Step 2: Wire timestamps into admin page route files.**\n115\t\n116\tTask 5.1 already modifies these 3 route files to add TTC list. Now also pass timestamps into the render calls. For each of these routes:\n117\t- `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/route.ts`\n118\t- `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_integrity/route.ts`\n119\t- `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_reports/route.ts`\n120\t\n121\tAdd `await getLastUpdatedTimestamps()` call and pass the result to the render function. The render functions accept these as template parameters — check each render.ts file's function signature to see where they go. Legacy passes them as `user_summary_last_updated_datetime` and `user_integrity_last_updated_datetime` (see `admin.py:239-240`).\n122\t\n123\t### Read These Files (for Step 2)\n124\t3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/render.ts` (first 20 lines) — render function signature\n125\t4. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/admin/ttc_applicants_integrity/render.ts` (first 20 lines) — render function signature\n126\t5. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/admin/ttc_applicants_reports/render.ts` (first 20 lines) — render function signature\n127\t6. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/.agent/tasks/TASK_ORDER.md` (Group 7 entry) — confirm execution sequence before coding.\n128\t\n129\t### Verification\n130\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n131\t- Commit message: `feat: add GCS-backed last-updated timestamps to admin pages`\n132\t\n133\t---\n134\t\n135\t## Task 3: Add Auth to Admin HTML Page Routes\n136\t\n137\t- Slug: `admin-page-auth`\n138\t- Goal: Add page-specific authentication to all admin HTML page routes.\n139\t\n140\t### Read These Files First\n141\t1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth-middleware.ts` — `requireAdminForPage()` function\n142\t2. All admin route files under `app/api/admin/*/route.ts` — identify which serve HTML pages (import from `render.ts`) vs which serve JSON data\n143\t\n144\t### Changes Required\n145\t\n146\tAdd `requireAdminForPage()` to each HTML page route. The pattern:\n147\t```typescript\n148\timport { requireAdminForPage } from '../../../utils/auth-middleware';\n149\t\n150\texport async function GET(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n151\t  const auth = await requireAdminForPage(request, 'PAGE_KEY.html');\n152\t  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n153\t\n154\t  // ... existing render logic ...\n155\t}\n156\t```\n157\t\n158\t**Page-specific auth mapping:**\n159\t\n160\t| Route file | Page key |\n161\t|---|---|\n162\t| `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/route.ts` | `ttc_applicants_summary.html` |\n163\t| `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_reports/route.ts` | `ttc_applicants_reports.html` |\n164\t| `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_integrity/route.ts` | `ttc_applicants_integrity.html` |\n165\t| `app/api/admin/settings/route.ts` | `admin_settings.html` |\n166\t| `app/api/admin/post_ttc_course_feedback/route.ts` | `post_ttc_course_feedback_summary.html` |\n167\t| `app/api/admin/post_sahaj_ttc_course_feedback/route.ts` | `post_sahaj_ttc_course_feedback_summary.html` |\n168\t| `app/api/admin/reports_list/route.ts` | `ttc_applicants_reports.html` |\n169\t| `app/api/admin/permissions/route.ts` | **NO AUTH — skip this one** |\n170\t\n171\t**`/api/admin/permissions`** must remain publicly reachable — it IS the unauthorized UX page.\n172\tDo not add `requireAdminForPage()` (or any other auth guard) to this route.\n173\t\n174\t### Verification\n175\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n176\t- Commit message: `feat: add page-specific auth to admin HTML page routes`\n177\t\n178\t---\n179\t\n180\t## Task 4: Auth + New Routes for User-Report Endpoints\n181\t\n182\t- Slug: `user-report-routes`\n183\t- Goal: Add auth to existing user-report route and create 2 missing user-report routes that admin pages need.\n184\t\n185\t### Read These Files First\n186\t1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/reporting/user-report/get-user-application-html/route.ts` (full file) — existing route, needs auth added\n187\t2. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/reporting/user_report.py` (lines 271-498) — `get_user_application()` and route handlers\n188\t3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts` — `TTCPortalUser` for loading user data\n189\t4. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth-middleware.ts` — `requireAdmin()`\n190\t5. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/render.ts` (lines 190-210) — shows how admin JS calls these endpoints (relative URLs)\n191\t\n192\t### Changes Required\n193\t\n194\t**Modify `app/api/admin/reporting/user-report/get-user-application-html/route.ts`:**\n195\tAdd `requireAdmin(request)` check at the start of GET handler.\n196\t\n197\t**Create `app/api/admin/reporting/user-report/get-user-application/route.ts`:**\n198\t\n199\t**IMPORTANT:** This route returns RENDERED HTML, not raw JSON. Legacy `user_report.py:271-467` renders form questions with user's answers as an HTML page using Jinja templates.\n200\t\n201\t**DEPENDENCY NOTE:** Full legacy-parity rendering requires country-specific form schemas from GCS (`config/forms/{country}/{form_type}.json`), which the plan defers to Phase 6. For Phase 5, use a simplified approach:\n202\t\n203\t```typescript\n204\timport { requireAdmin } from '../../../../../utils/auth-middleware';\n205\timport { TTCPortalUser } from '../../../../../utils/ttc-portal-user';\n206\t\n207\texport async function GET(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n208\t  const auth = await requireAdmin(request);\n209\t  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n210\t\n211\t  const url = new URL(request.url);\n212\t  const email = url.searchParams.get('email') || '';\n213\t  const formType = url.searchParams.get('form_type') || '';\n214\t  const formInstance = url.searchParams.get('form_instance') || '';\n215\t\n216\t  const user = await TTCPortalUser.create(email);\n217\t  const formData = user.getFormData(formType, formInstance);\n218\t\n219\t  // Phase 5 approach: render a simple key-value HTML table from stored form data.\n220\t  // This does NOT use country-specific form schemas (deferred to Phase 6).\n221\t  // When Phase 6 adds GCS schema loading, this renderer will be upgraded to show\n222\t  // proper question labels, field types, and display values.\n223\t  const rows = Object.entries(formData)\n224\t    .map(([key, val]) => `<tr><td>${key}</td><td>${String(val)}</td></tr>`)\n225\t    .join('');\n226\t  const html = `<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead><tbody>${rows}</tbody></table>`;\n227\t\n228\t  return new Response(html, {\n229\t    headers: { 'content-type': 'text/html' },\n230\t  });\n231\t}\n232\t```\n233\t\n234\t**Create `app/api/admin/reporting/user-report/get-user-application-combined/route.ts`:**\n235\t\n236\tSame simplified approach — accepts multiple forms via `forms` query param (JSON array of `{email, form_type, form_instance}`), loads each user's form data, renders all as concatenated HTML tables. Full schema-driven rendering comes in Phase 6.\n237\t\n238\tThis route is actively called by admin pages (`ttc_applicants_summary/render.ts:202`, `ttc_applicants_reports/render.ts:444`). It MUST return valid HTML — the admin page embeds it in an iframe/modal. The simplified key-value table is functional (shows all data) even without pretty question labels.\n239\t\n240\t### Constraints\n241\t- Auth is `requireAdmin()` — no cron bypass, no page-specific permission (matching legacy `user_report.py:478`)\n242\t- Routes MUST be under `/api/admin/reporting/user-report/` — admin page JS calls them via relative URLs\n243\t- Return content as `text/html` for the `get-user-application` and `get-user-application-combined` endpoints.\n244\t\n245\t### Verification\n246\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n247\t- Commit message: `feat: add auth and missing user-report routes for admin pages`\n248\t\n249\t---\n250\t\n251\t## Task 5: Fix Test Fixture Endpoint Path\n252\t\n253\t- Slug: `fixture-fix`\n254\t- Goal: Fix incorrect endpoint path in test fixture.\n255\t\n256\t### Read These Files First\n257\t1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/test/fixtures/test-config.json` (line 26) — incorrect endpoint namespace\n258\t\n259\t### Changes Required\n260\t\n261\t**Modify `test/fixtures/test-config.json:26`:**\n262\t\n263\tChange:\n264\t```json\n265\t\"user_integrity_load\": \"/jobs/reporting/user-integrity/load\"\n266\t```\n267\t\n268\tTo:\n269\t```json\n270\t\"user_integrity_load\": \"/jobs/integrity/user-integrity/load\"\n271\t```\n272\t\n273\tThe legacy namespace is `/jobs/integrity/user-integrity/load`, not `/jobs/reporting/user-integrity/load`. The correct JSON key is `user_integrity_load` (not `integrity_load`).\n274\t\n275\t### Verification\n276\t- Run fixture-driven tests: they should no longer fail due to endpoint mismatch\n277\t- Commit message: `fix: correct test fixture endpoint path for integrity load`\n278\t\n279\t---\n280\t\n281\t## Task 6: Validate Data Shape Compatibility\n282\t\n283\t- Slug: `data-shape-validation`\n284\t- Goal: Verify that real GCS data shape matches what the client-side JS expects (DataTables, Select2).\n285\t\n286\t### Overview\n287\t\n288\tThis is a **verification-only task** (no code changes except fixes if mismatches found). Before removing `mock-data.ts`, we must confirm that the JSON payloads returned by the real reporting/integrity jobs match the shape of the mock data, field-by-field. Mismatches will silently break the admin UI.\n289\t\n290\t### Steps\n291\t\n292\t1. **Seed test data:** Upload form responses for 3+ test users via `/users/upload-form-data` with diverse form types and nested structures (repeaters, checkbox groups, etc.). Include at least one TTC evaluation form to trigger matching logic.\n293\t\n294\t2. **Run jobs:** Execute both reporting pipelines:\n295\t   - POST to `/jobs/reporting/user-summary/load` to generate `user_summary_by_form_type.json` and `user_summary_by_user.json`\n296\t   - POST to `/jobs/integrity/user-integrity/load` to generate `user_integrity_by_user.json`\n297\t\n298\t3. **Extract GCS outputs:** Download the generated JSON files from GCS:\n299\t   - `user_data/summary/user_summary_by_form_type.json` → compare against `MOCK_SUMMARY_DATA`\n300\t   - GET `/api/admin/reporting/user-summary/get-by-user` response → compare against the combined shape consumed by all three reporting pages (`MOCK_REPORTS_DATA`, `MOCK_POST_TTC_FEEDBACK_DATA`, and `MOCK_POST_SAHAJ_FEEDBACK_DATA`).  \n301\t     If the Phase 5+ implementation has become a direct read of `user_summary_by_user.json`, that file must already contain this combined shape.\n302\t   - `user_data/integrity/user_integrity_by_user.json` → compare against `MOCK_INTEGRITY_DATA`\n303\t   - GET `/api/admin/admin/get-config` response → compare against `MOCK_SETTINGS_DATA` shape (NOT the raw `config/admin_config.json` GCS file, which is a wrapper; the API response returns `raw_config` contents that match the mock shape)\n304\t\n305\t4. **Field-by-field comparison:** For each exported file, verify:\n306\t   - Top-level keys match (same field names in real vs mock)\n307\t   - Nested object/array structures match (properties on nested objects, array item shapes)\n308\t   - Data types are consistent (string, number, boolean, array, object — no unexpected nulls or mismatched types)\n309\t   - Example: if `MOCK_SUMMARY_DATA['form_type_x'][0]` has fields `{email, form_instance, reporting_status, ...}`, verify the real output has exactly those fields\n310\t   - If a field in the mock is a number (e.g., `evaluations_submitted_count`), the real output must produce a number, not a string\n311\t\n312\t5. **Fix mismatches (if any):** If the shape differs, it's likely a bug in the user-summary.ts or user-integrity.ts logic. Investigate and fix the job logic. Do NOT work around it by changing the mock data — the mock is the canonical shape spec.\n313\t\n314\t6. **Log findings:** Document any shape discrepancies, fixes applied, and confirmation that the final outputs match exactly.\n315\t\n316\t### Verification\n317\t\n318\t- All GCS-generated JSON files have the same shape as their mock equivalents\n319\t- No uncommitted code changes (verification only — if bugs were found and fixed, those would be separate commits on their own tasks)\n320\t- Commit message: None needed (verification task — no code to commit unless fixes were required in user-summary.ts or user-integrity.ts, in which case those are bug fixes on separate tasks)\n321\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5435e6a-d4e5-45d2-bbb5-9eb27f15a589","uuid":"19110e44-7d6e-40fd-b48c-a61c856b3162","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:56:05.808Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/.agent/tasks/task-5-admin-wiring.md","content":"# Phase 5 Admin Wiring — Task Reference\n\n## Global Rules\n- Working directory: `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment`\n- These tasks depend on Phases 1-4 being complete\n- Do NOT modify `app/utils/auth.ts`\n- Do NOT remove `mock-data.ts` until ALL mock imports are eliminated\n- Group 7 ordering (`5.1` → `5.2` → `5.3` and `5.5` after `5.1-5.4`) is binding for execution and should not be changed here.\n\n## Loop\n- Implement: read this file, do Task N. Run `npx tsc --noEmit`. Commit.\n- Review: read this file, check Task N. Fix or say \"all clean.\"\n- Max 3 review rounds per task.\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Wire Dynamic TTC List on Admin Pages\n\n- Slug: `ttc-list-wiring`\n- Goal: Replace hardcoded TTC list placeholders with dynamic GCS-backed TTC list on all 3 admin pages.\n\n### Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/route.ts` (full file) — has `DEFAULT_TTC_LIST_HTML` placeholder\n2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_integrity/route.ts` (full file) — same pattern\n3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_reports/route.ts` (full file) — same + `ttcCountryAndDates: '[]'`\n4. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/admin.py` (lines 82-138) — `get_ttc_list_html()` to port\n5. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts` — `readJson()`, `GCS_PATHS`\n\n### Changes Required\n\n**Create `app/utils/admin-helpers.ts`:**\nPort `get_ttc_list_html()` from `admin.py:82-138`. Reads TTC list from GCS, generates `<option>` HTML. Also return raw JSON for `ttcCountryAndDates` parameter.\n\n```typescript\nimport { readJson, GCS_PATHS } from './gcs';\n\n/**\n * Port of admin.py:82-138 get_ttc_list_html().\n * @param userHomeCountry - ISO country code for filtering (optional). Legacy uses display_countries\n *   field on each option to filter by user's home country (admin.py:102-105).\n */\nexport async function getTtcListHtml(userHomeCountry?: string): Promise<{ html: string; json: string }> {\n  const allOptions = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.TTC_COUNTRY_AND_DATES) as Array<Record<string, unknown>>;\n\n  // Filter options by display_countries (matching admin.py:102-105)\n  const options = allOptions.filter(option => {\n    if (userHomeCountry && Array.isArray(option.display_countries)) {\n      return (option.display_countries as string[]).includes(userHomeCountry);\n    }\n    return true; // no filtering if no country or no display_countries field\n  });\n\n  let optionsHtml = '';\n  for (let i = 0; i < options.length; i++) {\n    const option = options[i];\n    const selected = i === options.length - 1 ? 'selected' : '';\n    optionsHtml += `<option value=\"${option.value}\" ${selected}>${option.display}</option>`;\n  }\n  // Wrap in the same div structure as legacy admin.py:116-131\n  const html = `<div class=\"mt-[15px] mb-[23px]\">\n    <div class=\"tablebody\"><div name=\"ttc_list\" class=\"tablerow\">\n      <div class=\"tablecell\"><label for=\"ttc_list\">TTC</label>\n        <span class=\"smallertext\">Select the TTC from the dropdown</span></div>\n      <div class=\"tablecell\">\n        <select class=\"textbox\" id=\"ttc_list\" name=\"ttc_list\" onchange=\"load_table_data()\">\n          ${optionsHtml}\n        </select></div>\n    </div></div></div>`;\n  return { html, json: JSON.stringify(allOptions) }; // json uses ALL options (unfiltered, for client-side use)\n}\n```\n\n**Modify each of the 3 route files:** Replace hardcoded `DEFAULT_TTC_LIST_HTML` with `await getTtcListHtml()`.\n\nFor the reports page route (`ttc_applicants_reports/route.ts`), ALSO replace the hardcoded `ttcCountryAndDates: '[]'` with the `json` value returned from `getTtcListHtml()`:\n```typescript\nconst { html, json } = await getTtcListHtml();\n// ... use html for DEFAULT_TTC_LIST_HTML replacement\n// ... use json for ttcCountryAndDates: json\n```\n\n### Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n- Commit message: `feat: wire dynamic TTC list from GCS on admin pages`\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Wire Last Updated Timestamps\n\n- Slug: `timestamps`\n- Goal: Add real last-updated timestamps to admin pages (currently hardcoded or missing).\n\n### Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/admin.py` (lines 158-174) — `get_user_reporting_last_updated_datetime()` to port\n2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts` — `getFileMetadata()` function\n\n### Changes Required\n\n**Step 1: Add helper to `app/utils/admin-helpers.ts`:**\n```typescript\nexport async function getLastUpdatedTimestamps(): Promise<{\n  user_summary_last_updated_datetime: string;\n  user_integrity_last_updated_datetime: string;\n}> {\n  // Read file metadata for summary (by_form_type) and integrity (by_user) files\n  // Use file.getMetadata() → top-level `updated` field\n  // Format as 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS'\n  // Handle file-not-found gracefully (return empty string)\n}\n```\n\n**Note:** Integrity reads from `_by_user` (not `_by_form_type`) — see plan for legacy inconsistency note.\n\n**Step 2: Wire timestamps into admin page route files.**\n\nTask 5.1 already modifies these 3 route files to add TTC list. Now also pass timestamps into the render calls. For each of these routes:\n- `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/route.ts`\n- `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_integrity/route.ts`\n- `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_reports/route.ts`\n\nAdd `await getLastUpdatedTimestamps()` call and pass the result to the render function. The render functions accept these as template parameters — check each render.ts file's function signature to see where they go. Legacy passes them as `user_summary_last_updated_datetime` and `user_integrity_last_updated_datetime` (see `admin.py:239-240`).\n\n### Read These Files (for Step 2)\n3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/render.ts` (first 20 lines) — render function signature\n4. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/admin/ttc_applicants_integrity/render.ts` (first 20 lines) — render function signature\n5. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/admin/ttc_applicants_reports/render.ts` (first 20 lines) — render function signature\n6. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/.agent/tasks/TASK_ORDER.md` (Group 7 entry) — confirm execution sequence before coding.\n\n### Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n- Commit message: `feat: add GCS-backed last-updated timestamps to admin pages`\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Add Auth to Admin HTML Page Routes\n\n- Slug: `admin-page-auth`\n- Goal: Add page-specific authentication to all admin HTML page routes.\n\n### Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth-middleware.ts` — `requireAdminForPage()` function\n2. All admin route files under `app/api/admin/*/route.ts` — identify which serve HTML pages (import from `render.ts`) vs which serve JSON data\n\n### Changes Required\n\nAdd `requireAdminForPage()` to each HTML page route. The pattern:\n```typescript\nimport { requireAdminForPage } from '../../../utils/auth-middleware';\n\nexport async function GET(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n  const auth = await requireAdminForPage(request, 'PAGE_KEY.html');\n  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n\n  // ... existing render logic ...\n}\n```\n\n**Page-specific auth mapping:**\n\n| Route file | Page key |\n|---|---|\n| `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/route.ts` | `ttc_applicants_summary.html` |\n| `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_reports/route.ts` | `ttc_applicants_reports.html` |\n| `app/api/admin/ttc_applicants_integrity/route.ts` | `ttc_applicants_integrity.html` |\n| `app/api/admin/settings/route.ts` | `admin_settings.html` |\n| `app/api/admin/post_ttc_course_feedback/route.ts` | `post_ttc_course_feedback_summary.html` |\n| `app/api/admin/post_sahaj_ttc_course_feedback/route.ts` | `post_sahaj_ttc_course_feedback_summary.html` |\n| `app/api/admin/reports_list/route.ts` | `ttc_applicants_reports.html` |\n| `app/api/admin/permissions/route.ts` | **NO AUTH — skip this one** |\n\n**`/api/admin/permissions`** must remain publicly reachable — it IS the unauthorized UX page.\nDo not add `requireAdminForPage()` (or any other auth guard) to this route.\n\n### Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n- Commit message: `feat: add page-specific auth to admin HTML page routes`\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: Auth + New Routes for User-Report Endpoints\n\n- Slug: `user-report-routes`\n- Goal: Add auth to existing user-report route and create 2 missing user-report routes that admin pages need.\n\n### Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/reporting/user-report/get-user-application-html/route.ts` (full file) — existing route, needs auth added\n2. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/reporting/user_report.py` (lines 271-498) — `get_user_application()` and route handlers\n3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts` — `TTCPortalUser` for loading user data\n4. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth-middleware.ts` — `requireAdmin()`\n5. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/render.ts` (lines 190-210) — shows how admin JS calls these endpoints (relative URLs)\n\n### Changes Required\n\n**Modify `app/api/admin/reporting/user-report/get-user-application-html/route.ts`:**\nAdd `requireAdmin(request)` check at the start of GET handler.\n\n**Create `app/api/admin/reporting/user-report/get-user-application/route.ts`:**\n\n**IMPORTANT:** This route returns RENDERED HTML, not raw JSON. Legacy `user_report.py:271-467` renders form questions with user's answers as an HTML page using Jinja templates.\n\n**DEPENDENCY NOTE:** Full legacy-parity rendering requires country-specific form schemas from GCS (`config/forms/{country}/{form_type}.json`), which the plan defers to Phase 6. For Phase 5, use a simplified approach:\n\n```typescript\nimport { requireAdmin } from '../../../../../utils/auth-middleware';\nimport { TTCPortalUser } from '../../../../../utils/ttc-portal-user';\n\nexport async function GET(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n  const auth = await requireAdmin(request);\n  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n\n  const url = new URL(request.url);\n  const email = url.searchParams.get('email') || '';\n  const formType = url.searchParams.get('form_type') || '';\n  const formInstance = url.searchParams.get('form_instance') || '';\n\n  const user = await TTCPortalUser.create(email);\n  const formData = user.getFormData(formType, formInstance);\n\n  // Phase 5 approach: render a simple key-value HTML table from stored form data.\n  // This does NOT use country-specific form schemas (deferred to Phase 6).\n  // When Phase 6 adds GCS schema loading, this renderer will be upgraded to show\n  // proper question labels, field types, and display values.\n  const rows = Object.entries(formData)\n    .map(([key, val]) => `<tr><td>${key}</td><td>${String(val)}</td></tr>`)\n    .join('');\n  const html = `<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead><tbody>${rows}</tbody></table>`;\n\n  return new Response(html, {\n    headers: { 'content-type': 'text/html' },\n  });\n}\n```\n\n**Create `app/api/admin/reporting/user-report/get-user-application-combined/route.ts`:**\n\nSame simplified approach — accepts multiple forms via `forms` query param (JSON array of `{email, form_type, form_instance}`), loads each user's form data, renders all as concatenated HTML tables. Full schema-driven rendering comes in Phase 6.\n\nThis route is actively called by admin pages (`ttc_applicants_summary/render.ts:202`, `ttc_applicants_reports/render.ts:444`). It MUST return valid HTML — the admin page embeds it in an iframe/modal. The simplified key-value table is functional (shows all data) even without pretty question labels.\n\n### Constraints\n- Auth is `requireAdmin()` — no cron bypass, no page-specific permission (matching legacy `user_report.py:478`)\n- Routes MUST be under `/api/admin/reporting/user-report/` — admin page JS calls them via relative URLs\n- Return content as `text/html` for the `get-user-application` and `get-user-application-combined` endpoints.\n\n### Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n- Commit message: `feat: add auth and missing user-report routes for admin pages`\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: Fix Test Fixture Endpoint Path\n\n- Slug: `fixture-fix`\n- Goal: Fix incorrect endpoint path in test fixture.\n\n### Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/test/fixtures/test-config.json` (line 26) — incorrect endpoint namespace\n\n### Changes Required\n\n**Modify `test/fixtures/test-config.json:26`:**\n\nChange:\n```json\n\"user_integrity_load\": \"/jobs/reporting/user-integrity/load\"\n```\n\nTo:\n```json\n\"user_integrity_load\": \"/jobs/integrity/user-integrity/load\"\n```\n\nThe legacy namespace is `/jobs/integrity/user-integrity/load`, not `/jobs/reporting/user-integrity/load`. The correct JSON key is `user_integrity_load` (not `integrity_load`).\n\n### Verification\n- Run fixture-driven tests: they should no longer fail due to endpoint mismatch\n- Commit message: `fix: correct test fixture endpoint path for integrity load`\n\n---\n\n## Task 6: Validate Data Shape Compatibility\n\n- Slug: `data-shape-validation`\n- Goal: Verify that real GCS data shape matches what the client-side JS expects (DataTables, Select2).\n\n### Overview\n\nThis is a **verification-only task** (no code changes except fixes if mismatches found). Before removing `mock-data.ts`, we must confirm that the JSON payloads returned by the real reporting/integrity jobs match the shape of the mock data, field-by-field. Mismatches will silently break the admin UI.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Seed test data:** Upload form responses for 3+ test users via `/users/upload-form-data` with diverse form types and nested structures (repeaters, checkbox groups, etc.). Include at least one TTC evaluation form to trigger matching logic.\n\n2. **Run jobs:** Execute both reporting pipelines:\n   - POST to `/jobs/reporting/user-summary/load` to generate `user_summary_by_form_type.json` and `user_summary_by_user.json`\n   - POST to `/jobs/integrity/user-integrity/load` to generate `user_integrity_by_user.json`\n\n3. **Extract GCS outputs:** Download the generated JSON files from GCS:\n   - `user_data/summary/user_summary_by_form_type.json` → compare against `MOCK_SUMMARY_DATA`\n   - GET `/api/admin/reporting/user-summary/get-by-user` response → compare against the combined shape consumed by all three reporting pages (`MOCK_REPORTS_DATA`, `MOCK_POST_TTC_FEEDBACK_DATA`, and `MOCK_POST_SAHAJ_FEEDBACK_DATA`).  \n     If the Phase 5+ implementation has become a direct read of `user_summary_by_user.json`, that file must already contain this combined shape.\n   - `user_data/integrity/user_integrity_by_user.json` → compare against `MOCK_INTEGRITY_DATA`\n   - GET `/api/admin/admin/get-config` response → compare against `MOCK_SETTINGS_DATA` shape (NOT the raw `config/admin_config.json` GCS file, which is a wrapper; the API response returns `raw_config` contents that match the mock shape)\n\n4. **Field-by-field comparison:** For each exported file, verify:\n   - Top-level keys match (same field names in real vs mock)\n   - Nested object/array structures match (properties on nested objects, array item shapes)\n   - Data types are consistent (string, number, boolean, array, object — no unexpected nulls or mismatched types)\n   - Example: if `MOCK_SUMMARY_DATA['form_type_x'][0]` has fields `{email, form_instance, reporting_status, ...}`, verify the real output has exactly those fields\n   - If a field in the mock is a number (e.g., `evaluations_submitted_count`), the real output must produce a number, not a string\n\n5. **Fix mismatches (if any):** If the shape differs, it's likely a bug in the user-summary.ts or user-integrity.ts logic. Investigate and fix the job logic. Do NOT work around it by changing the mock data — the mock is the canonical shape spec.\n\n6. **Log findings:** Document any shape discrepancies, fixes applied, and confirmation that the final outputs match exactly.\n\n### Verification\n\n- All GCS-generated JSON files have the same shape as their mock equivalents\n- No uncommitted code changes (verification only — if bugs were found and fixed, those would be separate commits on their own tasks)\n- Commit message: None needed (verification task — no code to commit unless fixes were required in user-summary.ts or user-integrity.ts, in which case those are bug fixes on separate tasks)\n","numLines":321,"startLine":1,"totalLines":321}}}
